Iavan Pijoos, News24Joost van der Westhuizen (File, Conrad Bornman, Beeld) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Pretoria &ndash; Former Springbok legend&nbsp;Joost van der Westhuizen will be honoured with a public memorial service at Loftus Versveld on Friday.South Africans will get the chance to say their final goodbyes to the legendary scrumhalf.&nbsp;The 45-year-old died of motor neuron disease on Monday. He was diagnosed with the illness in 2011.Van der Westhuizen's health took a turn for the worse over the weekend and he was rushed to hospital.The former Springbok captain played 89 Tests for the Springboks between 1993 and 2003.He scored a then-Springbok record of 38 tries and is widely regarded as one of the game&rsquo;s finest-ever scrumhalves.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.